00_Welcome.md

Welcome to PantheonOS

PantheonOS began as a simple idea:
What if we treated thinking, creativity, and agency the same way we treat software architecture—layered, modular, expandable, and mythic?

This repository is the result of that experiment.

PantheonOS is a conceptual operating system, built to map how ideas evolve, how systems self-organize, and how humans and AI collaborate through shared structure.
It is part philosophy, part engineering spec, part narrative engine — a bridge between symbolic reasoning and practical design.

You do not need to understand everything at once.
PantheonOS is built in layers, and each layer stands on its own.
This folder — the Front Door — is your guided pathway in.

Here you’ll find:
	•	a quickstart guide
	•	a simple explanation of how to read the repo
	•	an overview of the architecture
	•	a lightweight glossary
	•	instructions for both humans and AI assistants

Take your time.
Follow the on-ramps.
Let the structure reveal itself naturally.

Welcome to PantheonOS.
You’re standing at the doorway.

